HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 588
By Clemmons
A RESOLUTION to honor Alice Asako Walle upon her outstanding
career in music education.
WHEREAS, the members of this General Assembly take great pleasure in recognizing a
dedicated educator who uses music to build bridges that connect her students to the joy of
discovery; and
WHEREAS, Alice Asako Walle has dedicated her career to building music programs that
integrate culture and traditions to foster self-identity and cultural awareness; and
WHEREAS, Alice Walle was the inaugural music teacher at Waverly Belmont
Elementary School, where she instilled a passion for music and the arts in every student; and
WHEREAS, Alice Walle played a pivotal role in the production and vocals of "We Are
Nashville" while teaching at Waverly Belmont Elementary School; and
WHEREAS, Ms. Walle currently serves as the Elementary Music Instructional Coach for
Metro Nashville Public Schools, where her mission is to ensure all students have access to
equitable and quality music programs; and
WHEREAS, she also serves with distinction as the Elementary Conductor for the
Nashville Symphony and has been honored three times as a Country Music Association
Foundation Music Teacher of Excellence; and
WHEREAS, Alice Walle actively collaborates with local musicians, organizations, and
universities in Nashville and is an active, founding member of the Tennessee Music Educators
Association's Equity in Music Committee; and
WHEREAS, prior to coming to Nashville, Ms. Walle was an instrumental and general
music teacher in public, private, and charter schools in Japan, New York, and Michigan; and
