WHEREAS, upon the completion of the school year, Alice Walle will be relocating to
Michigan, and we wish to bid her a fond farewell as she departs Nashville; and
WHEREAS, she will be sadly missed by our entire community and all the parents of the
students whose lives and educations she enriched through her exuberant love of music and
teaching; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that we honor Alice Asako Walle upon her outstanding career in music
education, thank her for her exemplary service to Metro Nashville Public Schools and its
students, commend her ongoing commitment to equity in music, and wish her all the best in her
new professional endeavors.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
